{
  "stem": "11801.4",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And perhaps, although she never said that, wondered what we would do with him, had we brought him to the United States.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] But the reality was that we did leave, eventually, in March of 1946.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "We got, we got passage on a cargo boat.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "At that time, there were no passenger ships.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "All the ships had been requisitioned for the army, for the soldiers.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "So there was no-- there were none, as far as I know, that were exclusively being used for passengers.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And there were just a handful of us on the ship who were not part of the crew or-- I don't know what this ship was carrying, and I really didn't care.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "My mother and I-- and we took one other child with us.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "Somehow, my mother had found out that this child had no one to accompany her, and she could not leave without being accompanied.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "This was a Jewish child.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "I have no idea where she unearthed this child.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "So-- but we-- she said that we would take care of this child, which we did.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "The other passengers were all war brides.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "There were maybe a dozen of them, all of them young, Belgian war brides, who were absolutely terrified of what they had [LAUGHS] let themselves in for.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And some even flirted with these, with, with, with the, with the crew, which I found absolutely incredible.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "But I often wondered how they fared, coming to this country and meeting their husbands, whose language they probably couldn't speak and meeting their in-laws and, you know, the whole family and this very strange way of life.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Nowadays, again, you know, nothing is strange.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
